\cos (b) - \cos (a) = 2\cdot \sin (\frac{a+b}{2})\cdot \sin(\frac{a-b}{2})
\cos (b) - \cos (a) = 2e^{i\frac{a+b}{2} + i\frac{a-b}{2}}
\cos (b) - \cos (a) = 2e^{ia}
\sin\theta
\exp(i\theta)
\theta=(a+b)/2
\theta=(a-b)/2
e^{i\theta}=\cos\theta+i\sin\theta
\cos\theta = \frac{e^{i\theta}+e^{-i\theta}}{2} \qquad \sin\theta = \frac{e^{i\theta}-e^{-i\theta}}{2} 
